\begin{equation}
S_N(x; \varphi) = 2^{N-1} P_N(x; \varphi) \quad \text{and} \quad T_N(x)
\end{equation}
have the same coefficients for degrees $k = 1, \ldots, N$. They may differ in the constant term.

Hence there exists $c(\varphi) \in \R$ such that
